1
00:00:07,791 --> 00:00:12,375
<i>♪ Opening Theme ♪</i>

2
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:49,958
[cricket chirping]

3
00:01:50,041 --> 00:01:54,708
[footsteps approaching]

4
00:01:54,791 --> 00:01:57,791
[Ryujiro] Like they say,
you gotta fight fire with fire.

5
00:01:57,875 --> 00:02:01,000
But Oniwakamaru is awaiting
execution. He's dangerous,

6
00:02:01,083 --> 00:02:03,791
and if he's let out, there's
no telling what he might do.

7
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:06,708
[shrieking]

8
00:02:06,791 --> 00:02:11,125
[Ryujiro] My missing arm
is whispering to me.

9
00:02:11,208 --> 00:02:14,750
It's whispering, "You gotta
kill those bastards for me."

10
00:02:14,833 --> 00:02:16,750
[metal clanking]

11
00:02:16,833 --> 00:02:20,083
[door creaking open]

12
00:02:20,166 --> 00:02:22,375
Good to see you, Oniwakamaru.

13
00:02:22,458 --> 00:02:25,083
I admire that
fierce face of yours.

14
00:02:25,166 --> 00:02:28,541
A face more beastly
than that of an animal.

15
00:02:28,625 --> 00:02:31,458
You and I are two of a kind,
Oniwakamaru.

16
00:02:31,541 --> 00:02:34,458
Fact is, we're so alike
we could be brothers.

17
00:02:34,541 --> 00:02:37,583
So let's go take 'em out.
You and me.

18
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:40,833
Let's annihilate all
the people who tormented you.

19
00:02:46,250 --> 00:02:50,666
[cricket chirping]

20
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:58,333
[bird cawing]

21
00:02:58,416 --> 00:03:00,166
[Fuu] Alright,
is everybody ready?

22
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:01,583
Remember, no holding back.

23
00:03:01,666 --> 00:03:04,458
Pull out everything you've got.
Even your secret stash.

24
00:03:04,541 --> 00:03:06,208
One, two...

25
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:09,416
Are you kidding? That's it?!

26
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:12,250
Hey, dude, you sure
you're not holding out on us?

27
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:14,791
Look who's talking.
What's with the acorns?

28
00:03:16,208 --> 00:03:18,333
Alright, that's enough.
You two made me a promise.

29
00:03:18,416 --> 00:03:20,083
You haven't forgotten, have you?

30
00:03:20,166 --> 00:03:22,833
Until we find the samurai
who smells of sunflowers,

31
00:03:22,916 --> 00:03:25,250
you two are not allowed
to kill each other.

32
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:27,041
Oh, yeah, the smelly guy.

33
00:03:27,125 --> 00:03:28,750
I've been meaning
to ask you about that.

34
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:30,041
Huh?

35
00:03:30,125 --> 00:03:31,625
Who is this samurai
who smells of sunflowers?

36
00:03:31,708 --> 00:03:32,708
Well, he--

37
00:03:32,791 --> 00:03:34,833
What the hell
is a sunflower anyway?

38
00:03:34,916 --> 00:03:35,708
Wait a minute.

39
00:03:35,791 --> 00:03:36,583
You don't know?

40
00:03:36,666 --> 00:03:37,625
It's a flower.

41
00:03:37,708 --> 00:03:38,916
So what do they
smell like?

42
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,166
Do you have
any other leads?

43
00:03:40,250 --> 00:03:41,291
A picture
or somethin'?

44
00:03:41,375 --> 00:03:42,333
What makes you think
he's around here?

45
00:03:42,416 --> 00:03:44,583
Oh, stop!

46
00:03:44,666 --> 00:03:47,708
[stomach grumbling]

47
00:03:48,875 --> 00:03:51,791
For right now,
let's get something to eat.

48
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:57,583
[bird cawing]

49
00:03:57,666 --> 00:04:01,625
[Fuu] Ta-da! Yakimanjuu.
A Joushuu specialty.

50
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:04,375
The question is:
how many do we each get

51
00:04:04,458 --> 00:04:06,708
if we split these
between the three of us?

52
00:04:06,791 --> 00:04:08,833
[Mugen] I'll kill you two
and eat them all myself.

53
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:11,750
Hey! What's with you anyway?

54
00:04:14,666 --> 00:04:17,541
[bird cawing]

55
00:04:17,625 --> 00:04:18,875
[Fuu yelling]
Hey, come back here!

56
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:20,208
--[Mugen] That damn thief
--[Fuu] Come back here.

57
00:04:20,291 --> 00:04:21,583
--just jacked my grub.
--Give me back my manjuu.

58
00:04:21,666 --> 00:04:24,250
It's called a filcher bird,
and now you know why.

59
00:04:24,333 --> 00:04:26,708
[Farmer 1] What are you saying?

60
00:04:26,791 --> 00:04:28,500
You mean to tell me
that those missing people

61
00:04:28,583 --> 00:04:30,375
were attacked by
some kind of ogre?

62
00:04:30,458 --> 00:04:33,166
[Farmer 2] Yeah. At least
that's what the rumors say.

63
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:35,625
Good heavens,
what a horrible story.

64
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:38,875
Wait a minute.
You're a samurai, aren't you?

65
00:04:39,791 --> 00:04:42,583
So, you're the one
who can kill that ogre for us.

66
00:04:42,666 --> 00:04:44,000
Yeah, that's right.

67
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:45,916
What? Oh, no. Not me.

68
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,791
I couldn't possibly.

69
00:04:47,875 --> 00:04:51,625
[Inuyama screaming] You mustn't
sneak up on me like that.

70
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:56,041
[laughing] I guess there are
cowardly samurais after all.

71
00:04:56,125 --> 00:04:59,208
Now listen.
If those rumors are true,

72
00:04:59,291 --> 00:05:00,875
then right now
those people are--

73
00:05:00,958 --> 00:05:03,333
[Mugen]
Probably being eaten alive.

74
00:05:03,416 --> 00:05:05,250
Hey, my dumplings.

75
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:06,833
[Mugen]
I heard you guys talking.

76
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:10,500
An evil ogre, huh?
You want me to kill it for you?

77
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,291
[awed exclaiming]

78
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,791
[Farmer 1]
That sure was amazing.

79
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:31,083
You're a real expert, sonny.

80
00:05:31,166 --> 00:05:34,500
Bet you were a student at some
big name dojo. Am I right?

81
00:05:34,583 --> 00:05:36,041
Yeah. Something like that.

82
00:05:36,125 --> 00:05:39,666
[Fuu] So! What's this
ogre killing business?

83
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:42,458
You think you're
some kind of legendary hero?

84
00:05:42,541 --> 00:05:43,541
Listen, you're going to keep

85
00:05:43,625 --> 00:05:45,375
that promise you
made me, understand?

86
00:05:45,458 --> 00:05:48,125
Now calm down.
Don't get angry.

87
00:05:48,208 --> 00:05:49,916
Come join us. Have a seat.

88
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:54,208
I hate to say it, but I've
got to admit, I'm jealous.

89
00:05:54,291 --> 00:05:56,458
Of self-confident people,
I mean.

90
00:05:56,541 --> 00:06:01,250
You see, a guy like me
is samurai in name only.

91
00:06:06,541 --> 00:06:07,708
That's good.

92
00:06:07,791 --> 00:06:09,083
What kind of water is this?

93
00:06:09,166 --> 00:06:11,666
Wow. A real drinker, huh?

94
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:14,083
[Fuu moaning]

95
00:06:14,166 --> 00:06:14,958
Guess not.

96
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:16,958
Young man, you don't plan to go

97
00:06:17,041 --> 00:06:18,791
through the
mountains today, do you?

98
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:20,125
Yeah. So what?

99
00:06:20,208 --> 00:06:22,333
I wouldn't if I were you,
not at this hour.

100
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:24,000
The sun's about to go down.

101
00:06:24,083 --> 00:06:27,375
Perhaps, but we have
no money to pay for lodging.

102
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:31,500
I see. Well in that case, I know
the perfect place for you.

103
00:06:31,583 --> 00:06:34,333
There's a small, unoccupied
shack near the hot springs

104
00:06:34,416 --> 00:06:37,166
just up the road where
you can stay free of charge.

105
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:38,416
So why not spend the night there

106
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:40,833
and start your journey
tomorrow morning?

107
00:06:40,916 --> 00:06:44,833
[wood creaking,
Fuu snoring softly]

108
00:06:44,916 --> 00:06:47,583
[Mugen] Look at the dumb broad.
She's out cold.

109
00:06:47,666 --> 00:06:50,125
Let's strip her and dump her.

110
00:06:50,208 --> 00:06:51,500
That innkeeper back there...

111
00:06:51,583 --> 00:06:52,500
Eh?

112
00:06:52,583 --> 00:06:55,458
Forget it.
It's probably nothing.

113
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:56,583
Huh?

114
00:06:56,666 --> 00:07:01,791
[wood creaking]

115
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:09,833
[quiet clacking]

116
00:07:16,083 --> 00:07:17,166
[Ryujiro] Good work.

117
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:19,500
You followed
my instructions perfectly.

118
00:07:19,583 --> 00:07:21,291
Of course, Sir.

119
00:07:21,375 --> 00:07:23,583
Well I'll be running along now.

120
00:07:23,666 --> 00:07:26,250
[Ryujiro] Oh, I forgot
to mention one thing...

121
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:30,458
...Just to be safe,
I'm afraid, I gotta kill you.

122
00:07:30,541 --> 00:07:32,041
[gasping]

123
00:07:39,291 --> 00:07:41,958
Thanks very much.
That sure helped a lot.

124
00:07:42,041 --> 00:07:43,666
[Mugen] Who said
I did it for free?

125
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:45,000
Huh?

126
00:07:45,083 --> 00:07:46,833
What do you want?

127
00:07:46,916 --> 00:07:48,375
What do you got?

128
00:07:58,541 --> 00:08:05,208
[wood creaking]

129
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:10,041
Later. I gotta go
take care of something.

130
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:13,875
[Jin] That woman, huh?

131
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:21,500
Why'd you invite me?

132
00:08:21,583 --> 00:08:23,875
My goodness,
what a silly question.

133
00:08:23,958 --> 00:08:25,708
When a woman invites
a man to her home

134
00:08:25,791 --> 00:08:27,958
and they're all by themselves,

135
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:32,500
there aren't that many things
they can do, are there?

136
00:08:32,583 --> 00:08:34,791
Damn lady,
you move quick, don't you?

137
00:08:34,875 --> 00:08:37,500
[Hotaru] I'm not interested
in playing the coy maiden.

138
00:08:37,583 --> 00:08:40,500
Let's enjoy ourselves tonight.

139
00:08:40,583 --> 00:08:45,333
Nights are like the lives of
human beings, all too brief.

140
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:58,041
[wood creaking, Fuu snoring]

141
00:09:01,208 --> 00:09:02,500
Hey there.

142
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:03,500
[gasping]

143
00:09:04,916 --> 00:09:08,833
I think you should
go back to sleep for a while.

144
00:09:08,916 --> 00:09:09,875
[Fuu grunts]

145
00:09:10,541 --> 00:09:15,833
[sloshing water,
crickets chirping]

146
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:17,083
[Inuyama] Evening.

147
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:19,250
Isn't this a nice surprise?

148
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:21,875
[Jin] You're the man
from the teahouse.

149
00:09:28,041 --> 00:09:29,208
[Inuyama]
Beautiful, aren't they?

150
00:09:29,291 --> 00:09:31,708
Do you know why
fireflies glow like that?

151
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:33,791
It's a form of communication.

152
00:09:33,875 --> 00:09:37,500
Signals sent by the males and
females to attract one another.

153
00:09:37,583 --> 00:09:40,125
However, they say
that every once in a while

154
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:43,000
a male will try
to attract another male.

155
00:09:46,416 --> 00:09:49,208
Time to go.

156
00:09:49,291 --> 00:09:51,083
[Inuyama] Oh, that reminds me.

157
00:09:51,166 --> 00:09:54,041
I realize now
that I have heard of him.

158
00:09:54,125 --> 00:09:59,000
You know, the sunflower samurai
that the young lady spoke of?

159
00:10:03,791 --> 00:10:05,583
[Saruhashi] Ryujiro Sasaki!

160
00:10:08,791 --> 00:10:10,625
Kanto region police.

161
00:10:10,708 --> 00:10:13,916
Ryujiro Sasaki, 
you're under arrest for arson,

162
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,708
malicious destruction,
and the cold-blooded murder

163
00:10:16,791 --> 00:10:18,708
of a treasury employee.

164
00:10:19,416 --> 00:10:21,000
Now come along quietly.

165
00:10:21,083 --> 00:10:24,083
Well, now.
And here I thought I got away.

166
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:28,833
Be careful, Oniwaka. They want
to pick on you like the others.

167
00:10:28,916 --> 00:10:30,041
[gasping]

168
00:10:30,125 --> 00:10:31,416
Who the hell is that?

169
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:34,041
It doesn't matter who he is.
We'll take him down too.

170
00:10:34,125 --> 00:10:36,375
Right now. You big, ugly freak.

171
00:10:36,458 --> 00:10:37,958
[gasping]

172
00:10:40,583 --> 00:10:43,625
[fearful gasping]

173
00:10:43,708 --> 00:10:45,250
[screaming]

174
00:10:45,333 --> 00:10:46,541
[laughing]

175
00:10:46,625 --> 00:10:50,041
Stay away.
Stay away you damn monster!

176
00:10:50,125 --> 00:10:54,125
[screaming]

177
00:10:54,208 --> 00:10:56,541
[dying wail]

178
00:11:09,041 --> 00:11:10,666
[Oniwakamaru] Don't be afraid.

179
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:12,250
Huh?

180
00:11:12,333 --> 00:11:19,875
[Oniwakamaru] Everyone is afraid
of my face. They say it is ugly.

181
00:11:19,958 --> 00:11:24,375
They hate me.
They call me a monster.

182
00:11:24,458 --> 00:11:29,375
But if I do like this,
they cannot see my face.

183
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:36,500
[wood creaking]

184
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,458
No. Don't look at me.

185
00:11:49,958 --> 00:11:53,458
You're not scary,
but you do seem

186
00:11:53,541 --> 00:11:56,250
to have an awfully sad
look in your eye.

187
00:12:02,625 --> 00:12:08,000
[crowd yelling, jeering]

188
00:12:08,083 --> 00:12:11,833
[Oniwakamaru]
They called me a monster.

189
00:12:11,916 --> 00:12:16,333
I thought they were
going to kill me.

190
00:12:16,416 --> 00:12:22,708
I... I got angry.
I couldn't control myself.

191
00:12:22,791 --> 00:12:28,750
I... I killed many people.

192
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:33,291
I am all alone.

193
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,541
A firefly.

194
00:12:55,958 --> 00:12:58,375
[wood creaking]

195
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:03,666
It's all set.
I sent him his invitation.

196
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:07,208
Okay, Oniwaka,
let's get ready for the party.

197
00:13:17,458 --> 00:13:18,458
[surprised grunting]

198
00:13:19,083 --> 00:13:21,208
[Hotaru gasping]

199
00:13:21,291 --> 00:13:22,750
[spitting]

200
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:25,791
What the hell did you just
force me to swallow you bitch?

201
00:13:25,875 --> 00:13:28,333
[Hotaru chuckling]
Do you feel anything yet?

202
00:13:28,416 --> 00:13:30,416
It was a one-night mushroom.

203
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:33,041
Ordinarily,
it's harmless enough,

204
00:13:33,125 --> 00:13:36,416
but combined with sake
it's a deadly poison.

205
00:13:38,875 --> 00:13:39,916
[gasping]

206
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,708
Who the hell you workin' for?

207
00:13:41,791 --> 00:13:43,333
Better start talking quick
'cause I might just

208
00:13:43,416 --> 00:13:44,875
slice you up by mistake.

209
00:13:44,958 --> 00:13:46,625
A one-armed man
gave me the mushrooms

210
00:13:46,708 --> 00:13:49,250
and told me what to do.
He's got the antidote and

211
00:13:49,333 --> 00:13:52,708
something else
you want even more.

212
00:13:52,791 --> 00:13:53,708
What?

213
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:55,750
That girl
you were traveling with.

214
00:13:55,833 --> 00:13:57,041
I wonder what he'll do to her.

215
00:13:57,125 --> 00:13:58,458
Shit.

216
00:14:01,666 --> 00:14:02,791
[Jin] How much farther?

217
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:05,000
[Inuyama] We're almost there.

218
00:14:08,708 --> 00:14:10,416
[breathing heavily]
Damn it.

219
00:14:12,416 --> 00:14:15,083
[Inuyama sighing]

220
00:14:15,166 --> 00:14:19,791
I neglected to mention this
earlier, but I am an assassin.

221
00:14:19,875 --> 00:14:21,833
Yes, I already know that.

222
00:14:25,916 --> 00:14:28,333
I'd like you to know
I've enjoyed your company

223
00:14:28,416 --> 00:14:30,375
and bear you no ill will.

224
00:14:30,458 --> 00:14:34,166
For me, killing is merely a
business. It's nothing personal.

225
00:14:36,875 --> 00:14:43,500
[breathing heavily]

226
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:45,833
Son of a...

227
00:14:45,916 --> 00:14:47,375
Huh?

228
00:14:50,791 --> 00:14:52,458
Who hired you?

229
00:14:52,541 --> 00:14:56,166
Well, it's getting late. Perhaps
we should get started, huh?

230
00:14:59,625 --> 00:15:05,625
<i>♪ hip hop music ♪</i>

231
00:15:05,708 --> 00:15:10,291
[laughing] My, oh my,
the rumors were true.

232
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:11,833
You're quite good.

233
00:15:11,916 --> 00:15:15,125
It's been a while since I faced
a master swordsman like you.

234
00:15:23,166 --> 00:15:26,250
Guess I'll be doing
some ogre slaying after all.

235
00:15:31,583 --> 00:15:34,000
[Mugen] You bastard.

236
00:15:34,083 --> 00:15:35,583
[Fuu] Mugen!

237
00:15:35,666 --> 00:15:38,583
[Ryujiro] So you finally turned
up, huh? I figured you would.

238
00:15:38,666 --> 00:15:41,250
Now I'm gonna make you pay
for cuttin' off my arm.

239
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:42,333
Say what?

240
00:15:42,416 --> 00:15:44,208
You know what I'm talking about.

241
00:15:44,291 --> 00:15:48,000
You're the one. And don't try
telling me you don't remember.

242
00:15:48,083 --> 00:15:50,250
Sorry dude, but who are you?

243
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:53,625
[Ryujiro inhaling] Bastard!

244
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:59,500
Ah, I see. I've got to admit,

245
00:15:59,583 --> 00:16:01,625
you're much better
than I expected.

246
00:16:01,708 --> 00:16:06,083
In fact, if we were in a dojo,
I might not be able to beat you.

247
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:07,625
However...

248
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:21,791
Is there something wrong?

249
00:16:21,875 --> 00:16:25,208
It isn't the same
as fighting in a dojo is it?

250
00:16:25,291 --> 00:16:30,250
[Oniwakamaru yelling]

251
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:33,416
[Mugen] This sucks.
My arms are like wet noodles.

252
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:35,083
Mugen.

253
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:36,458
[Ryujiro] What's wrong?

254
00:16:36,541 --> 00:16:39,583
The poison you swallowed
finally starting to kick in?

255
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:40,916
You wanna live?

256
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,125
Got the antidote right here.

257
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:45,958
Know why they're called
one-night mushrooms?

258
00:16:46,041 --> 00:16:48,541
Because before you die,
you spend the whole night

259
00:16:48,625 --> 00:16:50,500
in unbearable agony.

260
00:16:50,583 --> 00:16:53,791
So by this time tomorrow,
you won't be around anymore.

261
00:16:53,875 --> 00:16:56,208
[Ryujiro laughing]

262
00:16:56,583 --> 00:16:58,541
[Mugen yelling]

263
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:13,166
[Oniwakamaru panting]

264
00:17:13,250 --> 00:17:20,125
I am ugly.
Don't look at me. AAARGH!

265
00:17:20,208 --> 00:17:21,500
[Mugen] Huh?

266
00:17:22,666 --> 00:17:23,708
Mugen!

267
00:17:23,791 --> 00:17:25,083
[Oniwakamaru crying]

268
00:17:25,166 --> 00:17:28,500
[Ryujiro] Not yet, Oniwaka.
Don't kill him just yet.

269
00:17:28,583 --> 00:17:32,375
That son of a bitch
is gonna die nice and slow.

270
00:17:32,458 --> 00:17:34,000
[Inuyama] I haven't
enjoyed myself this much

271
00:17:34,083 --> 00:17:36,958
in quite some time.
Nevertheless, I'd like to be

272
00:17:37,041 --> 00:17:41,083
as efficient as possible, which
means never working overtime.

273
00:17:42,208 --> 00:17:45,916
It's been fun, but I'm going to
end this now if you don't mind.

274
00:17:49,916 --> 00:17:51,958
[cloth tearing]

275
00:17:54,625 --> 00:17:57,750
How do you like that?
Can't breathe, can you?

276
00:17:57,833 --> 00:18:02,125
But I won't let you die yet. You
haven't suffered nearly enough.

277
00:18:02,208 --> 00:18:04,750
Now you're gonna
suffer some more.

278
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:08,708
[Fuu grunting, Ryujiro yelling]

279
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:13,500
Now it's your turn bitch.

280
00:18:13,583 --> 00:18:16,125
[Fuu gasping]

281
00:18:16,208 --> 00:18:19,125
Even better...
I'll make him suffer more

282
00:18:19,208 --> 00:18:21,666
by killing you first.

283
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:24,041
And you call yourself
a human being?

284
00:18:24,125 --> 00:18:25,333
Huh?

285
00:18:25,416 --> 00:18:28,625
[Ryujiro laughing]
Whatever gave you that idea?

286
00:18:28,708 --> 00:18:33,958
Young lady, I gave up
my humanity long, long ago.

287
00:18:34,041 --> 00:18:36,791
I like to watch human suffering.

288
00:18:36,875 --> 00:18:38,875
Now that's what I call fun.

289
00:18:38,958 --> 00:18:41,416
I'm really a very generous man.

290
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:44,416
I want to share my suffering
with everyone else.

291
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:47,333
I'd say that's fair,
wouldn't you?

292
00:18:47,416 --> 00:18:51,666
So, now you know why
you're gonna die.

293
00:18:51,750 --> 00:18:56,166
[gagging]

294
00:18:56,250 --> 00:18:59,041
Oniwaka... what are you...

295
00:18:59,125 --> 00:19:08,666
[choking]

296
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:10,208
[bones breaking]

297
00:19:15,375 --> 00:19:16,541
[Oniwakamaru roaring]

298
00:19:16,625 --> 00:19:18,708
No, don't!

299
00:19:18,791 --> 00:19:20,541
Don't do it!

300
00:19:27,125 --> 00:19:33,958
[crickets churping]

301
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:36,000
Oh, dear.

302
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:39,791
[Inuyama sighing]

303
00:19:41,791 --> 00:19:43,625
[Inuyama] What an odd
turn of events.

304
00:19:43,708 --> 00:19:46,333
It appears that my client
has just been dispatched.

305
00:19:46,416 --> 00:19:47,041
[Jin] What?

306
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:48,291
In other words,

307
00:19:48,375 --> 00:19:51,125
now I have absolutely
no reason to kill you.

308
00:19:51,208 --> 00:19:53,125
Clearly there's no point
in killing someone

309
00:19:53,208 --> 00:19:56,125
if I'm not going to make
any money by doing so.

310
00:19:56,208 --> 00:19:57,958
Well, I'm off.

311
00:20:01,708 --> 00:20:04,041
[Inuyama] I expect that
someday, somewhere,

312
00:20:04,125 --> 00:20:07,125
you and I will meet again.

313
00:20:07,208 --> 00:20:09,791
In fact, I'm sure we will.

314
00:20:24,541 --> 00:20:32,750
[Fuu] Why? Why did you
protect me? Tell me why.

315
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:40,541
You were the only one not
afraid to look at my face.

316
00:20:40,625 --> 00:20:46,708
Now I am not alone anymore.

317
00:21:41,750 --> 00:21:46,708
<i>♪ End Theme ♪</i>

